{
  "doc_id": "9605",
  "text": "Parotid gland tumor is one of the most common neoplasms in the head and neck region, and nearly about 50-100% patients with parotid tumor undergo Frey's syndrome (FS) after parotidectomy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Half of them have noticed symptoms and feel the gustatory sweating. About 13-23% patients consider their symptoms troublesome and severe [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
